tional argument (for example, `1234`, `https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/pull/1234`). If the user says \"review this PR\" without an argument, infer the PR from the surrounding conversation or `gh pr status`; only ask the user when it cannot be inferred. Use `gh pr view <pr>`, `gh pr diff <pr>`, and `gh pr checks <pr>` against the resolved PR throughout the workflow below.\n./skills/close-new-library-support-pr/SKILL.md:3:description: Close or reject pull requests that add support for a new library in graalvm-reachability-metadata. Use when asked to close a `library-new-request` PR and roll the linked issue back by removing assignees and changing project status from `In Progress` to `Todo` without downgrading `Done`.\n./skills/close-new-library-support-pr/SKILL.md:70:     - every project item and its status\n./skills/close-new-library-support-pr/SKILL.md:84:5. Roll project status back only when it is currently `In Progress`.\n./skills/close-new-library-support-pr/SKILL.md:128:   - Leave any other status unchanged unless the user explicitly asks otherwise.\n./skills/close-new-library-support-pr/SKILL.md:136:   - In this repository's main board today, the project is `oracle` project `30` titled `GraalVM Reachability Metadata`, and the status names are `Todo`, `In Progress`, and `Done`. Still query live data instead of hardcoding IDs.\n./skills/close-new-library-support-pr/SKILL.md:139:   - For each project item currently at `In Progress`, set the status to the `Todo` option:\n./skills/close-new-library-support-pr/SKILL.md:170:- If the issue belongs to multiple projects, only edit the project items that are currently `In Progress`; do not rewrite unrelated statuses.\n./skills/close-new-library-support-pr/SKILL.md:175:Keep status updates short and operational:\n./stats/com.charleskorn.kaml/kaml-jvm/0.104.0/stats.json:14:        \"ratio\" : 0.554741,\n./stats/com.charleskorn.kaml/kaml-jvm/0.104.0/execution-metrics.json:10:    \"status\": \"success\"